.TH SDL_CreateWindowWithProperties 3 "SDL 3.0.0" "SDL" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_CreateWindowWithProperties \- Create a window with the specified properties\[char46]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "SDL_Window* SDL_CreateWindowWithProperties(SDL_PropertiesID props);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
These are the supported properties:


\(bu "always-on-top" (boolean) - true if the window should be always on top

\(bu "borderless" (boolean) - true if the window has no window decoration

\(bu "focusable" (boolean) - true if the window should accept keyboard input
  (defaults true)

\(bu "fullscreen" (boolean) - true if the window should start in fullscreen
  mode at desktop resolution

\(bu "height" (number) - the height of the window

\(bu "hidden" (boolean) - true if the window should start hidden

\(bu "high-pixel-density" (boolean) - true if the window uses a high pixel
  density buffer if possible

\(bu "maximized" (boolean) - true if the window should start maximized

\(bu "menu" (boolean) - true if the window is a popup menu

\(bu "metal" (string) - true if the window will be used with Metal rendering

\(bu "minimized" (boolean) - true if the window should start minimized

\(bu "mouse-grabbed" (boolean) - true if the window starts with grabbed mouse
  focus

\(bu "opengl" (boolean) - true if the window will be used with OpenGL
  rendering

\(bu "parent" (pointer) - an 
.BR SDL_Window
 that will be the parent
  of this window, required for windows with the "toolip" and "menu"
  properties

\(bu "resizable" (boolean) - true if the window should be resizable

\(bu "title" (string) - the title of the window, in UTF-8 encoding

\(bu "transparent" (string) - true if the window show transparent in the areas
  with alpha of 0

\(bu "tooltip" (boolean) - true if the window is a tooltip

\(bu "utility" (boolean) - true if the window is a utility window, not showing
  in the task bar and window list

\(bu "vulkan" (string) - true if the window will be used with Vulkan rendering

\(bu "width" (number) - the width of the window

\(bu "x" (number) - the x position of the window, or
  
.BR
.BR SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED
, defaults to
  
.BR
.BR SDL_WINDOWPOS_UNDEFINED
\[char46] This is relative to
  the parent for windows with the "parent" property set\[char46]

\(bu "y" (number) - the y position of the window, or
  
.BR
.BR SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED
, defaults to
  
.BR
.BR SDL_WINDOWPOS_UNDEFINED
\[char46] This is relative to
  the parent for windows with the "parent" property set\[char46]

On macOS:


\(bu "cocoa\[char46]window" (pointer) - the (__unsafe_unretained) NSWindow associated
  with the window, if you want to wrap an existing window\[char46]

\(bu "cocoa\[char46]view" (pointer) - the (__unsafe_unretained) NSView associated with
  the window, defaults to [window contentView]

On Windows:


\(bu "win32\[char46]hwnd" (pointer) - the HWND associated with the window, if you want
  to wrap an existing window\[char46]

\(bu "win32\[char46]pixel_format_hwnd" (pointer) - optional, another window to share
  pixel format with, useful for OpenGL windows

On X11:


\(bu "x11\[char46]window" (number) - the X11 Window associated with the window, if you
  want to wrap an existing window\[char46]

The 
.BR SDL_Window
 is implicitly shown if the "hidden" property
is not set\[char46]

Windows with the "tooltip" and "menu" properties are popup windows and have
the behaviors and guidelines outlined in
.BR SDL_CreatePopupWindow()
\[char46]

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I props
the properties to use
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the window that was created or NULL on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR SDL_CreateWindow (3),
.BR SDL_DestroyWindow (3)
